rComments: Work hard, he actually ask questions about his course content!

For this class, would recommend understanding the slides and do practice questions on Anki. His test are mostly MCQ (online format). Attending DGD is highly recommended also for good practice problem and a good review of the class. Make sure to really understand the material and to study after each class. Very hard to cram it.
Good prof however online adaptation wasn't the best. Required you to do a lot outside of class and you had to watch lectures from past years in order to fully grasp the material.

You have to remember tiny details from lectures cause all the tests are pretty much that. Take it in English if you can. The powerpoint slides have no real structure, it just feels like he says a lot and nothing is actually learned.

I took this class during the pandemic. He responded to none of my emails and gave different exercises in the discussion groups vs labs. We had no idea what would be on the exam, he also put things we had never seen on the exam. His exam has about 10 options per question which makes it impossible to do well eve if you know your stuff.

I found that especially during this pandemic he was annoying with his redistribution of points given the fact that he chose to cancel the third midterm it was pretty unfair that he chose to add points to the other midterms while the other English prof added it to the final. He was punishing his students by ensuring that they get a low final grade.

He talks way too fast in class so it can be really hard to keep up with him. He isnt the best person to email either given the fact that he takes super long to answer and because his responses are pretty rude sometimes. I regret taking the class with him and not in English.
Never heard a prof talking that fast. Could barely understand him. He definitely has to slooooow down.
Tough grader . Seems extremely picky on what he wants on exams . Class average is always low
Horrible absolutely terrible !!!!

Worst class. Exam was very difficult and the average very low. It was written to be extremely long so it would be impossible to review it. Plus he gave a lot of calculus that are has long than the written part in the multiple choices. It was made long to make us purposely fail. He doesn't have our best interest at all.
Very long and difficult exams. Plus he is not really clear when answering questions you have to dig more

Les examens sont très longs . Il donne des mi-session dignes d examens finaux sachant que pour les finaux on a deux fois plus de temps pour le faire. Je m étais bien préparé mais jai foiré à cause de la longueur inappropriée de lexamen . Il ne faisait pas ça les autres années selon ses anciens examen. Très décevant je lene reprandrais plus jamais

Very long exams . Even if the material is easy once you understand the exam is a nightmare . He gave us 5 minutes bonus to continue but it was not enough. The multiple choices are full of calculus ( which was actually not the case the other years). The written part was also very long. He is not very clear in his explanation . Overall horrible

He puts a lot of effort into being a good prof, looks like he has greatly improved over the past few years. His midterms arent complicated and there are no surprises but they are very long so don't waste any time. Classes are recorded and he writes a lot of additional comments under his slides. He's pretty clear about whats relevant and what isnt.

FX is a great teacher, everything is clear about his lectures, there is no iffy stuff. On top of the slides, there are already notes at the bottom of the slides, clearing up any potential questions. Exams are long but not that hard, and reflect exactly what was seen in class. Class VODs are uploaded online so you can catch up if needed.

One of the most caring profs I've ever had, and he really wants you to succeed. He takes the feedback he receives into consideration, as he removed the negative correction on his MCQs. He also reuses past exams all the time which is really helpful when studying as you know what to expect. His diapos can be a bit scattered, but overall he was great!

His lectures were interesting and he took the time to ask if we had any questions. The PowerPoints were a little scattered but if you took good notes in class, you should be able to study well. Uses the same exams as previous years so practicing off of them is beneficial. The final was all about proteins (a previous section), which wasn't fair.

Biochem is not an easy subject for most students so don't let the bad comments get to you. He is an EXCELLENT professor who can answers every questions with no hesitation. He wants you to do great, even though you have to work for it. He records every class so you can re listen to it anytime. I would not take this class with any other teacher.
It's a tough class but he's not that bad. Really nice and caring. Slides are a little long and you sometimes get lost in the details. Reuses variations of past exams. Answers questions really well.

The professor gives sold lectures. Beware, he is very strict on the answers he accepts on his tests. You better have exactly what he has on his corrected version especially all the key words or you won't get many points. The exams are very long so work fast. The lab reports are very long and you will spend a lot more time on format than content.
Avoid at all cost. His diapos are full of mistakes and his classes are very but very desorganized. He doesn't  even answer his messages. His exams are difficult as he uses negative correction.

Ok professor.  Exams are super hard and the material for the exams is not clear at all. Multiple choice questions on the exams are worth 3 points and have multiple answers and was negative correction. Over all horrible class. Would not recommend.
It was is first year and he was okay. The final was hard but the midterms and the lab portion were good.

His multiple choice questions suck because theres always the possibility of having more than one answer. An average amount of effort is required in this class. If you attend class and go over the notes you can finish with a good grade. I never studied in this class not even for the final but I made sure to understand and I still finished with a B.

This prof was new but as a first time teacher he did a pretty good job. Biochem is an insanely hard class to begin with but Dr. Valois does his best to focus on the important slides/material. Work very hard and you'll get good grades but don't expect hundreds, it is BCH after all. On the plus side, the prof is pretty hot.

Le cours est plutôt difficile, mais le professeur est excellent. Il insère des notes sous les diapositives qui sont très utiles pour mieux comprendre la matière. Il prend le temps pour traduire toutes les figures sur les diapositives. Les cours sont très chargés, mais il connaît bien la matière et il est capable de la rendre intéressante.

Well he's a nice a guy at least. His first year teaching and he's not the best at it. PowerPoints and exams are TERRIBLY written (basically google translated) and it's easy to get lost in what you're reading. The class is hard, and unclear expectations and course notes make it so much harder. He's willing to answer questions though.
BCH2733 is not an easy class. With him ; (BCH2733 is not an easy class)^3.

He's a really good prof, he wants you to make sure you understand the course. You have to do some homework online, it's pretty simple plus if he sees you didn't do well he will make more so you can try to boost your grade. He usually makes a revision before exams to show you the most important things to work on. He's always there to answer question

Very new Prof and you can tell. Though the class was in French, all the homework, which were mandatory, were online and only offered in English. His exams seemed as if they were translated using Google Translate and lacked clarity. Same thing with his notes. Very easy to lose points on the multiple choice portion of his midterms.
